    "Similarly, let Y be the random variable for an instance of the output, y.",
    "To measure the influence of input x on output y, a good metric is the mutual information (Depeweg et al., 2018; Malinin and Gales, 2018) which measures how the output changes due to variation in the input.",
    "Thus we can define I(Y; X) a measure of the total input influence.",
    "Similarly we can define the influence from an individual element, X j, I(Y; X j) and it should obey:",
    "For each element X j, its influence is always determined by two components: X (s) j, the semantic information and a relating linguistic realization method which turns an abstract meaning into natural language."
